addAdmin(address).details: This function can only be called by the contract founder to add a new admin.

params._newAdmin: The address of the new admin

burn(uint256).details: Burns the NFT and alters some counters

claimMintPass(uint8[2],bytes,string[]).details: Users must provide the number of mintpasses they want to claim, along with the tokenURIs and a signature from our delegated server address. We then verify that the server did indeed sign a message approving them to claim the amount of mint passes. We use passesClaimed as a part of the message and increment it to ensure they cannot use the same signature multiple times.

params._tokenURIs: Token URIs for each of the mintpasses a user claims
params.numToMint: The number of mintpasses to claim. The first element in the array is the number of AI Champion mintpasses and the second element is the number of Dendroid mintpasses.
params.signature: The signature from the delegated server address

constructor.details: Initializes the smart contract with the founder and delegated addresses Also sets the founder as an admin by default

removeAdmin(address).details: Remove existing admins from the mapping (Founder-Only)

params.adminAddress: An address to remove from the mapping

params._state: The new paused state to set

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the tokenURI for a given token id

totalSupply().details: Informs the user of the total number of NFTs outstanding (non-burned)

transferOwnership(address).details: This function gives the founder the ability to transfer ownership to another address At the time of setting a new founder address, the old founder is removed as an admin

params._newFounderAddress: The new address which will have control over the smart contract

claimMintPass(uint8[2],bytes,string[]).notice: This allows you to claim a mintpass which you have qualified for
